        "You never know when inspiration will strike, or when or where you'll encounter some of the best words of wisdom you'll ever come across.",
      summary:
        "You never know when inspiration will strike, or when or where you'll encounter some of the best words of wisdom you'll ever come across. While I don't know who wrote this note for others to see, I saw the note when my friend Kim Brunson posted it to Facebook and it got me to thinking about how strange life can be. Wisdom and messages of Faith can truly find their way to you in the most unusual fashion!\nHere's what the note that was found posted in a laundromat in Lindale, TX, had to say:\n*I Am Just Saying*Thank God every morning and always do your best.It can be hard at times, but try.And always, when you are talking to someone, make sure your last words are kind, loving words and up lifting words, because you don't know if they might be your last words.\nP.H. I am just saying.",
